The Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has denied sending a letter to the Zamfara State chapter of the party aimed at sanctioning some of its members in the state. The party, in a statement on Thursday, by its Deputy National Publicity Secretary, Yekini Nabena, said the letter was forged and asked members in the state to disregard it. “The document should be disregarded. The mandate and focus of the Governor Mai Mala Buni-led APC Caretaker Committee is to bring all aggrieved party members to the table to achieve peace and bring all party members together and remains resolute in achieving this mandate,” the party said. The Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has denied sending a letter to the Zamfara State chapter of the party aimed at sanctioning some of its members in the state. The party, in a statement on Thursday, by its Deputy National Publicity Secretary, Yekini Nabena, said the letter was forged and asked members in the state to disregard it. “The document should be disregarded. The mandate and focus of the Governor Mai Mala Buni-led APC Caretaker Committee is to bring all aggrieved party members to the table to achieve peace and bring all party members together and remains resolute in achieving this mandate,” the party said.